list.name: Default Changelist
list.comment: Going to make the first roll out from here.

task.summary: Default task
Added Total column to the scope
Added commentary
Added an update timesheet routine
Added FIXME commentary for tomorrow.
Changed colors and fixed the last row issue with the scope. Going to add the Entity now.
Sucessfully added the Entity. Getting the entity does slow it down, so I changed the refresh time to 30 seconds, instead of 10 seconds.
Upgraded all version numbers. When this version gets published, I will need to make sure I copy EVERYTHING!
I believe I may have solved the issue with the EOD utility. It wasn't an issue with the EOD, but with the tardis not including the -o OUTTIME tag at the end of subprocess string.
Fixed an update issue with the daily total
Added Kill features to the time_lord() in order to try and fix the running queues on close.
Reworked the sheets but they still don't function. I may have to take a whole other approach.
Removing the Time Sheets Utility from the Tardis for the 0.4.6 release. I'll have to rework it for 0.4.7
Fixed minor string format error

Fixed an issue with opened lunch breaks. Minor fix, not rolling up numbers. There's still a trailing decimal for active lunches, but that's for another time since it only affects Panida at the moment.
Forgot to add the sleep number
Test crap
Setting up the next version number after release
Added Clockout button colorization and disabling to the Scope. Tool tips still don't work right

Cracked the Tool Tip nut, and it's not pretty: '

%s

' % variable. That's what you have to do to make the text black.
Sheets now puts out raw data with proper tool tip style sheets. Must go back and try something else with the widgets.
Going back to go forward
Have the User Start and Stop times set to more current data, instead of defaulting to the current time.
Making good progress with editable Time sheets.
Added tool tips to all the UI parts
Working on patching holes in the Lunch utility. Made improvements to the Time Lord UI. Made progress on Time Sheets UI, and gave an acronym to the TARDIS
Added a get next timesheet routine for the continuum and I think I fixed the lunch break glitch as well.
This version of sheets mostly works, except for the editor actions. I am considering a rewrite of the editor
Functional enough for now. I'll add the workers tomorrow.
Added integer check
Fixed the EOD utility for the Session clock outs. I should be able to put out 4.7 tomorrow.
Put to sleep a routine that opened the Time Lord first thing in the morning. It was redundant with the Unlock window doing it more efficiently.

Considering a new approach to this that may be slightly destructive to a process that's kind of working. I just fear this current method will have fatal flaws. It's already proving difficult to get data back from.
New method starting to work.
I got the Time Sheet and Editor to both edit and Delete records! A Net win for the day! Is it time to roll out 0.4.7? It might be...
Updated logging.
Removed the USER ID Tooltip formatting as it was causing an error, and no one really cares what it says anyways.
Partially reinstated the steady state and error state lights.
Reconnected sheets in the tardis and fixed a date issue with the sheets
Starting the 0.4.8 versions
Got reports added to the list
Added Daily Total to the Sheets. Changed text color in UI.
Commented out routines that made data calls, but then went nowhere. Also (mainly) added a check to see if the user is clocked in for the Lunch Break double checker
Added a "kill it" feature to the Lunch pop up.
Added improved thread closing to these files
Got the daily and weekly totals to display at the top of the Time Sheets. Must connect the manual timesheet add now.
Added "pretty_date_time" routine and implemented it in the Monitor Output
Got the manual card drop downs to work. It still does not create records, but it is mostly functional.
Replaced prints with logs and fixed the way it works.
Rolling up numbers for the 0.4.9 updates and fixes. Just rolled out 0.4.8
